36static int
37nvkm_ioctl_nop(struct nvkm_object *object, void *data, u32 size)
38{
39 union {
40 struct nvif_ioctl_nop_v0 v0;
41 } *args = data;
42 int ret;
43
44 nvif_ioctl(object, "nop size %d\n", size);
45 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
46 nvif_ioctl(object, "nop vers %"PRId64"\n", args->v0.version);
47 args->v0.version = NVIF_VERSION_LATEST;
48 }
49
50 return ret;
51}
52
53static int
54nvkm_ioctl_sclass(struct nvkm_object *object, void *data, u32 size)
55{
56 union {
57 struct nvif_ioctl_sclass_v0 v0;
58 } *args = data;
59 struct nvkm_oclass oclass;
60 int ret, i = 0;
61
62 nvif_ioctl(object, "sclass size %d\n", size);
63 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, true)) {
64 nvif_ioctl(object, "sclass vers %d count %d\n",
65 args->v0.version, args->v0.count);
66 if (size != args->v0.count * sizeof(args->v0.oclass[0]))
67 return -EINVAL;
68
69 while (object->func->sclass &&
70 object->func->sclass(object, i, &oclass) >= 0) {
71 if (i < args->v0.count) {
72 args->v0.oclass[i].oclass = oclass.base.oclass;
73 args->v0.oclass[i].minver = oclass.base.minver;
74 args->v0.oclass[i].maxver = oclass.base.maxver;
75 }
76 i++;
77 }
78
79 args->v0.count = i;
80 }
81
82 return ret;
83}

85static int
86nvkm_ioctl_new(struct nvkm_object *parent, void *data, u32 size)
87{
88 union {
89 struct nvif_ioctl_new_v0 v0;
90 } *args = data;
91 struct nvkm_client *client = parent->client;
92 struct nvkm_object *object = NULL;
93 struct nvkm_oclass oclass;
94 int ret, i = 0;
95
96 nvif_ioctl(parent, "new size %d\n", size);
97 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, true)) {
98 nvif_ioctl(parent, "new vers %d handle %08x class %08x "
99 "route %02x token %"PRIx64" object %016"PRIx64"\n",
100 args->v0.version, args->v0.handle, args->v0.oclass,
101 args->v0.route, args->v0.token, args->v0.object);
102 } else
103 return ret;
104
105 if (!parent->func->sclass) {
106 nvif_ioctl(parent, "cannot have children\n");
107 return -EINVAL;
108 }
109
110 do {
111 memset(&oclass, 0x00, sizeof(oclass));
112 oclass.client = client;
113 oclass.handle = args->v0.handle;
114 oclass.object = args->v0.object;
115 oclass.parent = parent;
116 ret = parent->func->sclass(parent, i++, &oclass);
117 if (ret)
118 return ret;
119 } while (oclass.base.oclass != args->v0.oclass);
120
121 if (oclass.engine) {
122 oclass.engine = nvkm_engine_ref(oclass.engine);
123 if (IS_ERR(oclass.engine))
124 return PTR_ERR(oclass.engine);
125 }
126
127 ret = oclass.ctor(&oclass, data, size, &object);
128 nvkm_engine_unref(&oclass.engine);
129 if (ret == 0) {
130 ret = nvkm_object_init(object);
131 if (ret == 0) {
132 list_add(&object->head, &parent->tree);
133 object->route = args->v0.route;
134 object->token = args->v0.token;
135 object->object = args->v0.object;
136 if (nvkm_client_insert(client, object)) {
137 client->data = object;
138 return 0;
139 }
140 ret = -EEXIST;
141 }
142 nvkm_object_fini(object, false);
143 }
144
145 nvkm_object_del(&object);
146 return ret;
147}

149static int
150nvkm_ioctl_del(struct nvkm_object *object, void *data, u32 size)
151{
152 union {
153 struct nvif_ioctl_del none;
154 } *args = data;
155 int ret;
156
157 nvif_ioctl(object, "delete size %d\n", size);
158 if (nvif_unvers(args->none)) {
159 nvif_ioctl(object, "delete\n");
160 nvkm_object_fini(object, false);
161 nvkm_object_del(&object);
162 }
163
164 return ret;
165}

186static int
187nvkm_ioctl_rd(struct nvkm_object *object, void *data, u32 size)
188{
189 union {
190 struct nvif_ioctl_rd_v0 v0;
191 } *args = data;
192 union {
193 u8 b08;
194 u16 b16;
195 u32 b32;
196 } v;
197 int ret;
198
199 nvif_ioctl(object, "rd size %d\n", size);
200 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
201 nvif_ioctl(object, "rd vers %d size %d addr %016"PRIx64"\n",
202 args->v0.version, args->v0.size, args->v0.addr);
203 switch (args->v0.size) {
204 case 1:
205 ret = nvkm_object_rd08(object, args->v0.addr, &v.b08);
206 args->v0.data = v.b08;
207 break;
208 case 2:
209 ret = nvkm_object_rd16(object, args->v0.addr, &v.b16);
210 args->v0.data = v.b16;
211 break;
212 case 4:
213 ret = nvkm_object_rd32(object, args->v0.addr, &v.b32);
214 args->v0.data = v.b32;
215 break;
216 default:
217 ret = -EINVAL;
218 break;
219 }
220 }
221
222 return ret;
223}
224
225static int
226nvkm_ioctl_wr(struct nvkm_object *object, void *data, u32 size)
227{
228 union {
229 struct nvif_ioctl_wr_v0 v0;
230 } *args = data;
231 int ret;
232
233 nvif_ioctl(object, "wr size %d\n", size);
234 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
235 nvif_ioctl(object,
236 "wr vers %d size %d addr %016"PRIx64" data %08x\n",
237 args->v0.version, args->v0.size, args->v0.addr,
238 args->v0.data);
239 } else
240 return ret;
241
242 switch (args->v0.size) {
243 case 1: return nvkm_object_wr08(object, args->v0.addr, args->v0.data);
244 case 2: return nvkm_object_wr16(object, args->v0.addr, args->v0.data);
245 case 4: return nvkm_object_wr32(object, args->v0.addr, args->v0.data);
246 default:
247 break;
248 }
249
250 return -EINVAL;
251}

253static int
254nvkm_ioctl_map(struct nvkm_object *object, void *data, u32 size)
255{
256 union {
257 struct nvif_ioctl_map_v0 v0;
258 } *args = data;
259 int ret;
260
261 nvif_ioctl(object, "map size %d\n", size);
262 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
263 bus_space_tag_t dummy __unused;
264 nvif_ioctl(object, "map vers %d\n", args->v0.version);
265 ret = nvkm_object_map(object, &dummy,
266 &args->v0.handle,
267 &args->v0.length);
268 }
269
270 return ret;
271}

292static int
293nvkm_ioctl_unmap(struct nvkm_object *object, void *data, u32 size)
294{
295 union {
296 struct nvif_ioctl_unmap none;
297 } *args = data;
298 int ret;
299
300 nvif_ioctl(object, "unmap size %d\n", size);
301 if (nvif_unvers(args->none)) {
302 nvif_ioctl(object, "unmap\n");
303 }
304
305 return ret;
306}

308static int
309nvkm_ioctl_ntfy_new(struct nvkm_object *object, void *data, u32 size)
310{
311 union {
312 struct nvif_ioctl_ntfy_new_v0 v0;
313 } *args = data;
314 struct nvkm_event *event;
315 int ret;
316
317 nvif_ioctl(object, "ntfy new size %d\n", size);
318 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, true)) {
319 nvif_ioctl(object, "ntfy new vers %d event %02x\n",
320 args->v0.version, args->v0.event);
321 ret = nvkm_object_ntfy(object, args->v0.event, &event);
322 if (ret == 0) {
323 ret = nvkm_client_notify_new(object, event, data, size);
324 if (ret >= 0) {
325 args->v0.index = ret;
326 ret = 0;
327 }
328 }
329 }
330
331 return ret;
332}

391static struct {
392 int version;
393 int (*func)(struct nvkm_object *, void *, u32);
394}
395nvkm_ioctl_v0[] = {
396 { 0x00, nvkm_ioctl_nop },
397 { 0x00, nvkm_ioctl_sclass },
398 { 0x00, nvkm_ioctl_new },
399 { 0x00, nvkm_ioctl_del },
400 { 0x00, nvkm_ioctl_mthd },
401 { 0x00, nvkm_ioctl_rd },
402 { 0x00, nvkm_ioctl_wr },
403 { 0x00, nvkm_ioctl_map },
404 { 0x00, nvkm_ioctl_unmap },
405 { 0x00, nvkm_ioctl_ntfy_new },
406 { 0x00, nvkm_ioctl_ntfy_del },
407 { 0x00, nvkm_ioctl_ntfy_get },
408 { 0x00, nvkm_ioctl_ntfy_put },
409 { 0x00, nvkm_ioctl_map_netbsd },
410};

412static int
413nvkm_ioctl_path(struct nvkm_client *client, u64 handle, u32 type,
414 void *data, u32 size, u8 owner, u8 *route, u64 *token)
415{
416 struct nvkm_object *object;
417 int ret;
418
419 if (handle)
420 object = nvkm_client_search(client, handle);
421 else
422 object = &client->object;
423 if (unlikely(!object)) {
424 nvif_ioctl(&client->object, "object not found\n");
425 return -ENOENT;
426 }
427
428 if (owner != NVIF_IOCTL_V0_OWNER_ANY && owner != object->route) {
429 nvif_ioctl(&client->object, "route != owner\n");
430 return -EACCES;
431 }
432 *route = object->route;
433 *token = object->token;
434
435 if (ret = -EINVAL, type < ARRAY_SIZE(nvkm_ioctl_v0)) {
436 if (nvkm_ioctl_v0[type].version == 0)
437 ret = nvkm_ioctl_v0[type].func(object, data, size);
438 }
439
440 return ret;
441}
442
443int
444nvkm_ioctl(struct nvkm_client *client, bool supervisor,
445 void *data, u32 size, void **hack)
446{
447 struct nvkm_object *object = &client->object;
448 union {
449 struct nvif_ioctl_v0 v0;
450 } *args = data;
451 int ret;
452
453 client->super = supervisor;
454 nvif_ioctl(object, "size %d\n", size);
455
456 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, true)) {
457 nvif_ioctl(object,
458 "vers %d type %02x object %016"PRIx64" owner %02x\n",
459 args->v0.version, args->v0.type, args->v0.object,
460 args->v0.owner);
461 ret = nvkm_ioctl_path(client, args->v0.object, args->v0.type,
462 data, size, args->v0.owner,
463 &args->v0.route, &args->v0.token);
464 }
465
466 nvif_ioctl(object, "return %d\n", ret);
467 if (hack) {
468 *hack = client->data;
469 client->data = NULL;
470 }
471
472 client->super = false;
473 return ret;
474}
